commit.message:
Fix equal signs escaping

According to InfluxDB line protocol documentation,
equal signs must be escaped as well as commas and spaces.
Otherwise it causes invalid tag format error when trying
to send tag containing one or more equal signs.
Link:
https://docs.influxdata.com/influxdb/v1.3/write_protocols/line_protocol_reference/#special-characters

Merge pull request #4 from sbi/allow-zero-values

Allow zero values

Encode line protocol to UTF8, make sure unicode (python 2) / str (python 3) input is not encoded to str (python 2) / bytes (python 3) prematurely.

str.format always returns an ascii string if the format string was ascii, no matter that the arguments were in unicode. Mixing str and bytes in a call to str.join() in Python 3 raises a TypeError.
Allow ClientBase to send points with zero value(s). Also fixes a bug where None values in a values dict would be encoded to „value=none“

Merge pull request #1 from bobo333/add_http_client

Adding Http Client

Make HttpClient Dependencies Optional

Requires specifying http during install to install HttpClient's dependencies.
Only imports HttpClient's dependencies if using HttpClient. This allows for the use of the standard TelegrafClient without having to install requests-futures.
